title: Roundup (Oct. 14): Friends beats No. 15 Boys' Latin, 3-1, in soccer
text:
Glenelg Country School 4, Key School 0: Alisha Netus had a goal and an assist to lead the visiting Dragons (10-0) past the Obezags (4-7). 
Glenelg Country School led 3-0 at halftime. 
Chapelgate Christian Academy 4, Concordia Prep 1: Jasa Curry had two goals and two assists to power the host Yellow Jackets (10-1) past the Saints (5-6-1). 
Field hockey 
No. 1 Archbishop Spalding 2, Roland Park 0: Erin Shanahan scored twice to power the Cavaliers (11-0-1) past the host Reds (6-6). 
Spalding outshot Roland Park 16-8. 
No. 2 Garrison Forest 3, St.Mary's 2: The visiting Grizzlies (11-1-1) escaped the Saints (6-3-2) as Hailey Mules completed her hat trick on a penalty corner draw with time expired. 
St. Mary's led 2-1 at the half. 
Notre Dame Prep 2, Bryn Mawr 0: Catherine Keirn had two goals and Emily Cooper had two assists to lead the Blazers (4-4) past the host Mawrtians (3-9-1). 
Annapolis Area Christian School 1, Glenelg Country School 0, OT: Sophia Kalaris made four saves for the visiting Dragons (6-5), but the host Eagles (10-4) prevailed. 
North Harford 1, Fallston 0, 2OT: Sarah Jackson's unassisted goal early in the second overtime lifted the Hawks (10-3, 6-0) over the visiting Cougars (7-5, 5-1). 
The win secured the UCBAC Chesapeake Division title, a first in program history.
